sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / DSP API Server
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Controller as workflow-controller<br/>Informer Watch
    participant StepPod as Step Pod + argoexec<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant S3 as S3/MinIO Object Store<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant DB as PostgreSQL/MySQL<br/>5432/3306 TCP

    Note over User,DB: Flow 1: Workflow Execution

    User->>K8sAPI: 1. Create Workflow CR<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: 2. Watch event (Workflow created)<br/>Informer, TLS 1.2+
    Controller->>K8sAPI: 3. Create Step Pod<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount Token
    Note over StepPod: Pod starts with argoexec<br/>init/sidecar container
    StepPod->>K8sAPI: 4. Report step status<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount Token
    StepPod->>S3: 5. Upload artifacts<br/>HTTPS/443, Access Key/Secret Key
    S3-->>StepPod: Artifact stored
    StepPod-->>K8sAPI: Step complete
    Controller->>K8sAPI: 6. Update Workflow status<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount Token

    Note over User,DB: Flow 2: Workflow Archival (Optional)

    Controller->>DB: 1. Archive completed workflow<br/>TCP 5432/3306, Username/Password
    DB-->>Controller: Archived

    Note over User,DB: Flow 3: Argo Server Query

    User->>K8sAPI: Query via Argo Server API
    Note over K8sAPI: argo-server pod<br/>Port 2746/TCP gRPC/HTTPS
    K8sAPI-->>DB: 2. Query archived workflows<br/>TCP 5432/3306, Username/Password
    DB-->>K8sAPI: Results
    K8sAPI-->>User: Workflow data

    Note over User,DB: Flow 4: CronWorkflow Scheduling

    Note over Controller: Cron ticker fires
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Workflow from CronWorkflow<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount Token
